headline: FPL flexes its muscle in Florida Legislature, but loses one out of three
author: Jeffrey Schweers
sentences: And it sent an army of lobbyists to the Florida Capitol to push measures in its favor and squash bills that could hurt its bottom line.
Ron DeSantis vetoed its signature bill that would have gutted net metering and saved FPL millions of dollars a year.
It salted the campaigns and political committees of Florida lawmakers and their parties with millions of dollars.
TALLAHASSEE  Florida Power & Light did everything by the corporate book on how to influence a legislature.
At first, it looked like it got everything it wanted from the Legislature.
It drafted priority legislation and handed it to lawmakers.
